    • Method Detail

      • onExecute

        protected final java.lang.String onExecute(SCUIContext uiContext)
        This method implements abstract method of SCUIAction. Internally this method calls #validateMashup(SCUIContext, boolean), #massageInput(Element, SCUIContext), #invokeMashup(Element, SCUIContext), and #massageOutput(Element, SCUIContext) methods. These methods can be extended in any class extending this class. SCUIAction#onExecute(SCUIContext)
        Specified by:
        onExecute in class SCUIAction

      • fetchActionResult

        protected java.lang.String fetchActionResult(org.w3c.dom.Element inputEl,
                                             org.w3c.dom.Element outputEl,
                                             SCUIContext context)
        This method is protected and currently fetches action result 'SUCCESS'. Any class extending SCUIXAPIMashupAction can extend this method and write custom logic of fetching action result.This the application to override to steer action result to a particular jsp based on the input or output element. inputEl is the input element outputEl is the output element context is of type SCUIContext action result 'SUCCESS'

      • invokeMashup

        protected org.w3c.dom.Element invokeMashup(org.w3c.dom.Element inputEl,
                                           SCUIContext uiContext)
        This method invokes mashup using SCUIMashupHelper inputEl of the type Element uiContext of the type SCUIContext output element

      • validateMashup

        protected boolean validateMashup(SCUIContext uiContext,
                                 boolean throwEx)
        This method validates mashup id provided as struts parameter. Currently this method just checks for a value; and does not do any real validation on mashup id. Any class extending this class can extend this method and write custom logic. uiContext throwEx pass true if this method should throw exception if validation fails. true if validation is successful.

      • massageInput

        protected org.w3c.dom.Element massageInput(org.w3c.dom.Element inputEl,
                                           SCUIContext uiContext)
        This method is protected and currently fetches input from the request. Any class extending SCUIXAPIMashupAction can extend this method and write custom logic of massaging input before actual XAPI mashup is called. inputEl uiContext is of type SCUIContext massaged input element

      • massageOutput

        protected org.w3c.dom.Element massageOutput(org.w3c.dom.Element outputEl,
                                            SCUIContext uiContext)
        This method is protected currently sets the output as attribute if outputNamespace is defined and returns the same output. Any class extending SCUIXAPIMashupAction can extend this method and write custom logic of massaging output from actual XAPI mashup invocation. outputEl of the type Element uiContext is of the type SCUIContext output element.

        public boolean acceptableParameterName(java.lang.String parameterName)
        Utility method which returns true if the action will accept the parameter with the given name.
